divs: Sighting DetailsI looked out my front window of my house this morning at 5:15am PST. In the distance (guessing 15-20 miles) I noticed a strange object the size of a star to the West of Bremerton, WA. What caught my eye was the fact that it was giving off a pulsing light. "That's no star!" I said as I went to retrieve my binoculars. Through the binoculars I could see red , green, and blue lights rotating around it. I watched it for about 10 minutes, then decided to grab my video camera...but the battery was dead. So I just watched it through the binoculars for about 30 minutes total until some low level clouds obscured it. Then I went back to bed. It remained motionless the entire time. I know this because I had a reference point (electrical line over the street) in which to observe any movement for the 30 minutes that I saw it. No movement was observed!
Summary: Multi colored lights rotating around the craft
trends: There have been no other sightings in Seabeck
